<br>
This is set up for clerics and non-clerics to respond.  Questions 1, 2, and 3 are for Clerics, and questions 4 and 5 are for non-clerics.<br>
<br>
As defined by Caster's Realm about Divine Aura:<br>
<br>
&quot;The caster gets 18 seconds of invulnerability. You cannot melee or cast spells during this time. This spell moves you to the bottom of an NPC's aggression list, meaning if there is someone else engaging it, it will turn on them.<br>
As of 5/8/01 you can no longer be stunned while this spell is active.<br>
<br>
You cannot be effected by beneficial spells either, meaning you cannot be healed or buffed. In order to cast or be cast upon before the spell wears off, you must cancel the spell by clicking on the spell icon. This spell takes 15 minutes to cycle.&quot;<br>
<br>
Here is an explanation of the choices below:<br>
<br>
1. (Clerics)  I never Divine Aura:  I would never, ever Divine Aura in a group because I will use my mana to the end trying to save a group.<br>
<br>
2. (Clerics) I would Divine Aura in a group only if all hope is lost, I have just enough mana to do it (takes like a sliver of mana), and you've done all that you can.  (For Response:  Would you feel guilty about it?)<br>
<br>
3. (Clerics)  It is my Diety-Given Right to Divine Aura, and if the party is going down that bad, then Divine Aura it is.<br>
<br>
4. (Non-Clerics) If there is no hope, and the Cleric is almost OOM, then they have done all they can.  They should Divine Aura.<br>
<br>
5. (Non-Clerics)  Clerics are for healing.  They should be the hero and remain until they are the last ones standing before they Divine Aura.  Or they should only use it to have uninterupted time to gain mana for more healing.<br>
<br>
