Vallaelanan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utiestooakey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tiesto Oakey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Shadowknight who says Ni!</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/6/01 1:19:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=62.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Using Divine Aura in Groups</span><hr size=1> When I was a cleric, I would DA/DB as soon as I had agro, however those were mobs that hit for double 250s + anything else I could tank nice (1050 unbuffed ac thnx) and didn't DA till it was last resort. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uverionbluehawk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Verion Bluehawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/6/01 4:53:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=62.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Using Divine Aura in Groups</span><hr size=1> For me as a cleric, there is no discussion really on this.<br>
<br>
Usually if a situation arises whereby you need to DA, then you will most likely have aggro. If your getting beat, you can't cast. If you can't cast, your just a lump of meat.<br>
<br>
It takes so little mana and time to cast that caasting DA in no way affects other members of the group, with the exception that it may allow the cleric to survive and lose aggro so they can heal again. I've found it to be an essential part of the cleric's equipment.<br>
<br>
I've never felt guilty for using this (though I always feel guiltly for running from battle). If I still have mana and someone desperatly needs a heal, I can always click it off and cast.<br>
<br>
