I see no problem with clerics using it, if they do it at inappropriate times and flee battle when all is not lost (till they flee) they will suffer the reputation of that (if it happens a lot). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalninil>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/9/01 1:39:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=62.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Using Divine Aura in Groups</span><hr size=1> With out a chanter, I've used DA to give the folks around my some time to establish hate. As for feeling guilty about useing it &lt;shrug&gt; only reason I'll have agro is if folks need heals and haven't established it. Stun and root are also in my arsonole and i don't feel guilt about rooting the mobs up by the tanks and backing off. Thats what they do, take damage and dish it out. My defences may be high ,but my armor, well lets say I've scrapped armor for wisdom. <br>
