It really depends on the situation, in some cases folks will sacrafice themselves knowing that you can res them once you get back. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/11/01 5:14:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=62.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   In a group ..</span><hr size=1> .. it is very nice for two people to survive in a shit-storm: the cleric and the corpse dragger.  The group can recover really quick and get back to xp'ing if the cleric lives.  Cleric dies and you need to wait on everyone.<br>
<br>
On normal servers, clerics can bind at the zone line, so it's not usually a huge hardship if they die.  Here, though, you'd have to wait for her to run back.  There are lots of other nice uses for DA, too, as some of the clerics mentioned here.<br>
<br>
One of my fav. clerics used to rush to the zone early when I called a bad pull incoming.  I'd hold stuff off (ogre war back then) while everyone got a head start.  She'd heal hurt folks (usually me) as we got in range, then use DA to get herself out.<br>
<br>
